secondary_outcome.description:
The parent/caregiver will also be asked to recall the number of bowel movements and the stool consistency seen most often over the 24-hour period. Pictures will be provided to the participant's parent or caregiver for use as a guide in rating the stool consistency.
Questionnaire: What stool consistency was seen most often in your baby's bowel movements over the past 24 hours?(Use pictures provided for reference) (0) No bowel movement;
Hard- dry, hard pellets;
Formed- definite shape, not dry;
Soft-no definite shape, pasty;
Unformed or seedy- no shape, some water or small lumps ;
Waterly- no shape, mainly water
For option 0~5, 0 and 1 represent poor stool Characteristics , 2-5 represent fine stool Characteristics.
